class aiofauna.faunadb.errors.ErrorData(code, description, position, failures, cause=None)[source]

Bases: object

Data for one error returned by the server.

cause

List of all Failure objects returned by the server.

None unless code == “validation failed”.

code

Error code. See all error codes here.

description

Error description.

failures

Cause of the error. May be None.

class aiofauna.faunadb.objects.Ref(id, cls=None, db=None)[source]

Bases: Expr

`python Ref(id, cls=None, db=None) ` A reference to a document in a collection or index.

Parameters:

  • id – The document’s ID.

  • cls – The collection or index class.

  • db – The database.

Ref

Is a special type in FaunaDB. It is used to represent a document in a collection or index.

It is serialized to JSON as an object with the @ref key. Passing the id to the response.

collection()[source]

Gets the collection part out of the Ref.

database()[source]

Gets the database part out of the Ref.

id()[source]

Gets the id part out of the Ref.
